I'll generate proficiency levels for each of the four culinary technique skills using the 3-level model (Foundational, Proficient, Expert). Let me create observable, mutually exclusive descriptions for each.

<function_calls>
<invoke name="add_proficiency_levels">
<parameter name="skills_json">[
  {
    "skill_name": "Knife Skills & Prep",
    "levels": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "level_name": "Foundational",
        "level_description": "Executes basic cuts (brunoise, julienne, dice) following established knife techniques while maintaining consistent safety protocols. Demonstrates proper grip, hand position, and claw hold under direct supervision for high-volume prep work."
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "level_name": "Proficient",
        "level_description": "Independently performs all standard knife cuts and specialty cuts (tourné, chiffonade) with precision and speed, adapting technique based on ingredient type and desired outcome. Mentors junior staff on proper form and consistently achieves quality benchmarks without supervision."
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "level_name": "Expert",
        "level_description": "Designs and optimizes prep workflows that reduce waste and processing time while maintaining zero safety incidents and superior quality across high-volume production. Innovates cutting techniques for specialty ingredients and sets kitchen standards for precision and efficiency."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "skill_name": "Heat Control & Cooking Techniques",
    "levels": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "level_name": "Foundational",
        "level_description": "Follows established cooking procedures for standard techniques (sauté, roast, simmer) and recognizes when dishes have reached proper doneness using visual and textural cues. Requires guidance to adjust heat and timing for non-routine situations or ingredient variations."
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "level_name": "Proficient",
        "level_description": "Independently applies a range of cooking methods with deliberate heat control to consistently achieve target flavors, textures, and doneness levels across varied ingredients and recipes. Troubleshoots cooking issues (overcooking, uneven browning) and adjusts technique in real-time to meet quality standards."
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "level_name": "Expert",
        "level_description": "Orchestrates complex multi-technique dishes and cooking sequences while managing heat distribution across stations, and innovates cooking methods that enhance flavor profiles and reduce preparation time. Mentors kitchen staff on advanced technique application and establishes department-wide cooking standards."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "skill_name": "Seasoning & Flavor Development",
    "levels": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "level_name": "Foundational",
        "level_description": "Identifies and applies basic seasonings (salt, pepper, herbs) according to recipe specifications and recognizes fundamental flavor balance (sweet, salty, acidic, umami). Requires guidance to adjust seasoning levels and develop more complex flavor profiles."
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "level_name": "Proficient",
        "level_description": "Independently develops well-balanced dishes by layering seasonings, adjusting acidity and richness, and creating complimentary sauces that enhance the primary ingredient. Analyzes dishes and makes precise adjustments to achieve target flavor profiles consistent with menu standards."
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "level_name": "Expert",
        "level_description": "Architects innovative flavor combinations and ingredient pairings that distinguish signature dishes and enhance the restaurant's culinary identity while maintaining ingredient quality and seasonal availability. Mentors team members on advanced flavor theory and establishes seasoning protocols that drive consistent excellence across the menu."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "skill_name": "Plating & Presentation",
    "levels": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "level_name": "Foundational",
        "level_description": "Follows plating guides and templates to present dishes with appropriate portion sizes and basic visual composition aligned with kitchen standards. Identifies presentation elements (color, balance, garnish) and applies them with supervision for consistency."
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "level_name": "Proficient",
        "level_description": "Independently composes visually appealing plates that balance color, height, and negative space while maintaining precise portion accuracy and executing garnish work with technical skill. Coordinates plating efficiency across service and ensures consistency with established plate designs."
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "level_name": "Expert",
        "level_description": "Designs signature plate presentations that elevate the dining experience and reflect the restaurant's culinary vision while optimizing plating workflows for speed and consistency during high-volume service. Mentors kitchen staff on advanced plating aesthetics and establishes presentation standards that distinguish the establishment in the market."
      }
    ]
  }
]</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

<function_calls>
<invoke name="finish">
<parameter name="result">Successfully generated 3-level proficiency frameworks for all 4 Culinary Technique skills:

1. **Knife Skills & Prep** — Foundational (follows with supervision) → Proficient (independent precision & mentoring) → Expert (design workflows, innovates techniques)

2. **Heat Control & Cooking Techniques** — Foundational (follows procedures) → Proficient (independent application & troubleshooting) → Expert (orchestrates complex sequences, innovates methods)

3. **Seasoning & Flavor Development** — Foundational (applies basic seasonings with guidance) → Proficient (develops balanced dishes independently) → Expert (architects signature flavors, mentors on theory)

4. **Plating & Presentation** — Foundational (follows templates with supervision) → Proficient (composes appealing plates independently) → Expert (designs signature presentations, establishes standards)

All levels follow the observable behavior model with clear action verbs and measurable outcomes. Levels are mutually exclusive and represent cumulative mastery across the progression.</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

