I'll generate proficiency levels for the two skills in the Food Safety & Kitchen Standards category using the 3-level model (Foundational, Proficient, Expert).

<function_calls>
<invoke name="add_proficiency_levels">
<parameter name="skills_json">[
  {
    "skill_name": "Food Safety & HACCP",
    "levels": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "level_name": "Foundational",
        "level_description": "Identifies and follows established food safety protocols, temperature controls, and basic HACCP procedures under supervision. Recognizes common contamination risks and documents compliance checks as directed."
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "level_name": "Proficient",
        "level_description": "Independently applies HACCP principles to identify critical control points, monitors temperatures and storage conditions, and implements corrective actions to prevent cross-contamination. Executes daily food safety documentation and trains junior staff on compliance procedures."
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "level_name": "Expert",
        "level_description": "Architects comprehensive HACCP systems, evaluates emerging food safety regulations, and optimizes kitchen protocols to exceed compliance standards across multiple preparation stations. Mentors teams on risk mitigation and drives organizational food safety culture through continuous process improvement."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "skill_name": "Kitchen Sanitation",
    "levels": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "level_name": "Foundational",
        "level_description": "Follows established sanitation schedules and procedures, cleaning workstations and equipment according to checklists. Recognizes when areas require attention and reports deviations to supervisors."
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "level_name": "Proficient",
        "level_description": "Independently manages daily sanitation routines, organizes cleaning workflows to minimize cross-contamination, and maintains equipment logs demonstrating compliance. Trains staff on proper sanitation techniques and adapts procedures based on audit feedback."
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "level_name": "Expert",
        "level_description": "Establishes kitchen sanitation standards that exceed regulatory requirements, integrates new cleaning technologies and protocols, and shapes sanitation practices across multiple kitchens. Conducts internal audits, mentors sanitation teams, and drives measurable improvements in hygiene metrics and compliance outcomes."
      }
    ]
  }
]</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

<function_calls>
<invoke name="finish">
<parameter name="result">Successfully generated proficiency levels for 2 skills in the Food Safety & Kitchen Standards category:

1. **Food Safety & HACCP** — 3 levels completed
   - Level 1 (Foundational): Follows protocols under supervision, recognizes risks
   - Level 2 (Proficient): Independently applies HACCP principles, implements controls, trains staff
   - Level 3 (Expert): Architects systems, evaluates regulations, mentors across organization

2. **Kitchen Sanitation** — 3 levels completed
   - Level 1 (Foundational): Follows schedules, recognizes deviations
   - Level 2 (Proficient): Manages routines independently, adapts based on feedback
   - Level 3 (Expert): Establishes standards, integrates new technologies, drives measurable improvements

All descriptions use observable action verbs and business outcomes appropriate to chef/kitchen operations. Levels are mutually exclusive and assume mastery of prior levels.</parameter>
</invoke>
</function_calls>

